  "local_port": 57856,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "When helping a user decide to buy an air conditioner (AC), it\u2019s important to ask probing questions that can guide them toward the best choice for their needs. Here are some relevant questions:\n\n1. **Room Size and Layout:**\n   - What is the size of the room or area where you plan to install the AC?\n   - Are there any large windows or doors in the room that might affect cooling?\n\n2. **Cooling Needs:**\n   - How many people typically occupy the space?\n   - Are there any heat-producing appliances in the room (e.g., ovens, computers)?\n\n3. **Climate Considerations:**\n   - What is the average temperature in your area during the summer months?\n   - How many months of the year do you expect to use the AC?\n\n4. **Type of AC System:**\n   - Are you looking for a window unit, a portable AC, or a central air conditioning system?\n   - Do you want a unit that can also provide heating?\n\n5. **Energy Efficiency:**\n   - How important is energy efficiency to you? \n   - Are you interested in any specific energy-saving features?\n\n6. **Budget:**\n   - What is your budget range for purchasing an AC unit?\n   - Are you considering the long-term costs of electricity and maintenance in your budget?\n\n7. **Noise Level:**\n   - How sensitive are you to noise? Do you prefer a quieter unit or is noise not an issue for you?\n\n8. **Installation:**\n   - Are you planning to install the unit yourself or would you prefer a professional installation?\n   - Do you have any specific requirements or restrictions regarding installation (e.g., building codes, landlord approvals)?\n\n9. **Features and Technology:**\n   - Are there any specific features you\u2019re interested in, such as smart controls, programmable timers, or air purification?\n   - How important is it for you to have a remote control or mobile app access?\n\n10. **Warranty and Support:**\n    - How important is a warranty or service agreement to you?\n    - Do you have any preferences regarding brand or manufacturer based on past experiences or recommendations?\n\nBy asking these questions, you can better understand the user\u2019s needs and preferences, which will help in recommending the most suitable air conditioning unit for them.",
